snippet.textDisplay: Every father loves his child and the relationship of a father and his daughter is somewhat extra special where he remains her hero all her life and at the same time he wants her to walk her life only on flowers. When Sharmilee is singing the opening verse and Babul is seen in the background, all we can see him doing is smile, but how many emotions that smile carries is something only a father can tell. He must be thinking of the time she was born in his hands, then changing her nappies, having sleepless nights when she was not so well, seeing her crawl, seeing her walk, seeing her off for the first time to her school and now seeing her here so big that she finally shares the stage with him. There’s no comparison between the love of a father and mother because if one is the heart, the other is the heartbeat. Seeing a life coming out of her body is the most magical moment for a mother and likewise when a father looks at his child, he feels that he/she is the most beautiful creation of his blood. While listening to this song all over again, I’m tearful this time for trying to feel all these emotions as I look at this lovely girl and her “Babul”...
